{
  "answer": "In *Andreas*, authority—here apostolic and heroic, as Christ's champion—is vested in the steadfast hero who endures torment unyieldingly through faith in God, praising the heavenly King amid chains and scourging without faltering.[^1] [^2] [^3] His worthiness manifests as divine favor: wounds heal miraculously, guards die at his prayer, and floods obey him, proving God's protection for the faithful servant.[^4]\n\nIn *Manusmṛti* Book 7, royal authority stems from justly wielding *daṇḍa* (the rod of punishment), which the king embodies as guarantor of *dharma* across castes and life-stages; he must be truthful, deliberate, wise in *dharma*-*artha*-*kāma*, and self-conquering to apply it without caprice.[^5] [^6] Such a king wins fame that \"spreads... like a drop of oil on water,\" while the opposite contracts \"like a drop of ghee on water\"; battlefield prowess appears in his protective duties, sense-conquest enabling subject-control, and conquest of enemies.[^7] [^8]\n\nNeither text recognizes the other's ideal: *Andreas* elevates suffering faith as heroic/divine authority against heathens, with no *daṇḍa*-like punitive mechanism; *Manusmṛti* grounds kingship in worldly order via measured force and self-mastery, sans Christian endurance or God-reliance.\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-da0c5e).\n\n[^2]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-34b202).\n\n[^3]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-dbf56f).\n\n[^4]: Cynewulf, *Andreas*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-e5fbef).\n\n[^5]: Unknown, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-c970b2).\n\n[^6]: Unknown, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-96ec46).\n\n[^7]: Unknown, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-7cf38b).\n\n[^8]: Unknown, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/#p-45020b).",
